<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">Three real paths, same destination: a locked exoplanet choice + a profile to defend.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can extract key habitability data from a card, justify why I chose this exoplanet, and identify two questions I'll need to answer about my chosen planet in Blocks 7–8.
    <ul class="success-criteria">
      <li>I can extract the key habitability data from an exoplanet card.</li>
      <li>I can justify my planet choice from that data.</li>
      <li>I can name two questions about my planet I'll need to answer in Blocks 7–8.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Solo profile build</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Pick your exoplanet from the table above. Fill in a one-page profile using the printed data card: distance, host star type, mass, radius, orbital period, atmospheric data status (observed / unknown), HZ status, one major uncertainty. End the page with one sentence: "I chose this planet because…"</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Independent · Solo</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Pair-debate Earth-like vs. Mars-like</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">With a partner who picked a different planet, debate: is your planet more Earth-like (atmosphere, water possibility, magnetic protection) or more Mars-like (lost atmosphere, frozen surface, no magnetic field)? Defend with at least three pieces of evidence from your data card. Then switch.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Verbal · Pair</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">AI-coached exoplanet interrogation</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Use the <a href="/ai-partners/planet-hunter/">Planet Hunter</a> to work through one specific uncertainty about your planet ("what does JWST not yet know about K2-18 b's atmosphere?" / "how confident is the Gliese 581 d detection?"). The Planet Hunter will push back — let it. Load the same planet in the <a href="/units/unit-1/habitability-zone-calculator/">Habitability Zone Calculator</a> as you talk — notice how Atmosphere = Unknown propagates as UNCERTAIN through the framework. Document the exchange in the <a href="/foundations/ai-documentation-protocol/">AI Documentation Template</a>.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Conversational · Solo</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

